body:
So, I recently got a problem. By recently, I mean literally today. I have 2 computers, one is a mac and the other is a Windows. Apparently, on my Windows computer, my ms used to be 46, staying there. Nothing weird, till I suddenly spiked to 700 MS while in a game and then sit flat on 106 or above. The only time it decides to change is if it wants to increase. I never had this problem before, and while I do play with WiFi ( i know its not a good idea to go wifi but its giving me 46 ms ), I have extenders too. So I'm almost as good as using a cable. This problem has only been encountered after 7.5, which I find weird because I am not the only one that only got this after 7.5, but I'm sure its different because  I didn't get it instantly after the update. This problem carried on to make it so I always have 106 MS on games.

On my Mac, it seems that my MS is normal. I don't have an amazing memory, so I might be wrong, but I think my Mac computer is better than my Windows at playing League. Think of it as my Mac is D2 and my Windows dropped from D5 to S3. However, I don't always get to use my Mac due to family issues (more of my mother going facebook mode on it and never stop), and I am loyal to Windows mostly. But it's vital to note that I am not the only one with this problem. 


